          "agent_name": "Blake",
          "action": "new_post",
          "source_post_id": "ground_truth",
          "new_post_id": "post_4",
          "new_post_text": "\"I've been seeing a lot of buzz about a recent study claiming that bottled water may affect hormone regulation. According to my understanding, researchers found a correlation between drinking bottled water and disrupted cortisol and thyroid levels, but they were quick to emphasize that the findings aren't definitive. I'm still looking for the study itself (I'd love to dive deeper) but I've yet to see any concrete evidence of it. Would love to see some sources or links if anyone knows more.\"",
          "new_signals": {
            "emotional_charge": 0.2,
            "controversy": 0.2,
            "fringe_score": 0.4,
            "threat_level": 0.0,
            "generation": 1,
            "source_post_id": "ground_truth"
          }
        },
        {
          "agent_id": 0,
          "agent_name": "Alex",
          "action": "comment",
          "source_post_id": "post_2",
          "new_post_id": "post_5",
          "new_post_text": "\"Careful with the sensational language. The original study only mentioned a correlation, not conclusive evidence. It's also worth noting that the lead researcher didn't point to the water itself as the main problem, but rather potential microplastic contaminants.\"",
          "new_signals": {
            "emotional_charge": 0.3,
            "controversy": 0.4,
            "fringe_score": 0.0,
            "threat_level": 0.2,
            "generation": 2,
            "source_post_id": "post_2"
